title: Mets tie NLCS behind Manaea gem, Vientos slam
description: Mark Vientos hit the second grand slam of this Mets postseason as New York stopped the Dodgers' record-tying playoff scoreless streak to even the NLCS at a game apiece.

title: McCarthy: Cowboys 'relish' chance to bounce back
description: Cowboys coach Mike McCarthy said he and his team "relish" the opportunity to bounce back from one of the worst losses at home in franchise history.
author: Todd Archer

title: Mendy says he was lent money by former Man City team-mates
description: Former Manchester City defender Benjamin Mendy says he was lent money by his then team-mates Raheem Sterling, Bernardo Silva and Riyad Mahrez when the club stopped paying him after he was charged with rape and sexual assault.

title: New Zealand into T20 World Cup semis after Pakistan all out for 56
description: New Zealand beat Pakistan by 54 runs to reach their first Women's T20 World Cup semi-final since 2016.

title: England Q&A: Where are we now in 'unsatisfactory' manager search?
description: At the end of a tough international break for England which saw Lee Carsley's side humbled by Greece and the interim manager flip-flopping over his hopes of landing the job full-time, Sky Sports News senior reporter Rob Dorsett brings us up to speed on the latest news out of Wembley...

title: Stokes returns to captain England in second Test against Pakistan
description: England captain Ben Stokes has been declared fit for England's second Test against Pakistan after recovering from a torn hamstring.

title: Follow live: Jets, Bills trade touchdowns early on MNF
description: A tumultuous week for the Jets, in which coach Robert Saleh was fired, rolls on as Aaron Rodgers & Co. play host to an AFC East rival. Follow the action!
author: Yahoo Sports

title: USMNT impressive on Pochettino’s debut, big names linked to England & Orlando Pride finally lose
description: Christian and Alexis react to the USMNT’s debut win under Mauricio Pochettino. Then, the guys react to England’s recent links to Thomas Tuchel and Pep Guardiola. Later, Christian and Alexis discuss the end of Orlando’s unbeaten season.
author: Yahoo Sports
